Description.LocalizedString: She imagined herself rising from the brush, her terrifying silhouette striking fear in her enemies' hearts.
She seemed to be one with the wilderness, determined to survive at all costs.
She stomped through the snow, and those who could run made their escape.
She imagined rising from the brush, her terrifying silhouette a reflection of the brutality of nature.
She seemed to be more beast than human, the price she paid for her survival.
She stomped through the snow, resolved to never stop moving forward.
A fashionable way to avoid eye damage from the sun or any particularly bright relics.
Among adventuring archaeologists, no shirt is more iconic.
A flash of color made the perfect accessory for her heavy, functional boots.
No matter where she went, the jacket made her feel like she was back in London on a crisp autumn day.
She could always rely on a tough and comfy pair of jeans to get her through most jobs.
The endless white could freeze you to the bone as quickly as it could rob you of your vision.
Extreme elements would never scare her away from the potential for a big find.
Even the most sure-footed adventurer could use some help on the ice.
She painted herself with the blood of a dead animal and disappeared into the trees.
She had a knack for quickly turning furs and skins into sturdy garments.
The water went up past her ankles, but her feet stayed warm and dry.
